Bug 1 — Scroll listener doesn't fire on iOS Safari
iOS Safari doesn't fire scroll events on window the same way desktop browsers do. It batches scroll events and delivers them after the momentum scroll completes, not during. The fix is two-part: add { passive: true } to the event listener (tells iOS it can scroll without waiting for your JS), and also listen on document as a fallback.
Bug 2 — Hamburger button too small and doesn't respond to taps
