Video vs GIF — The Real Answer
Use native video, not GIF. Here's why:
FormatFile sizeQualityMobileGIFHuge (5-20MB)Grainy, 256 colorsKills battery, slow loadMP4/WebMSmall (500KB-2MB)Full color, smoothHardware accelerated
A 10 second GIF is 15MB. The same clip as MP4 is 800KB and looks better. iOS and Android both handle <video autoPlay muted loop playsInline> perfectly — playsInline is the iOS Safari key that prevents fullscreen takeover.
The right setup:

Hero background → <video> tag instead of GIF
Gallery page → mix of <video> and <img> — browser handles both natively
Services preview → <video> instead of current GIFs
